---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Asteris Commerce — Australian indie WordPress + WooCommerce plugin company"
  description="Asteris Commerce builds five plugins: Asteris for WooCommerce (20 modules), Asteris for WordPress (11 modules), Asteris Cart (21-module checkout suite for WC), Asteris Affiliates (full affiliate program for WP + WC, in build), and Asteris Blocks (50 free Gutenberg blocks). Sydney-built. Small team. No VC, no growth team. One vendor, five plugins, honest about what we do and what we don't."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="eyebrow">★ Australian indie WP + WC plugin company</div>
      <h1>
        Four plugins.<br />
        <span class="accent">One vendor.</span><br />
        Built in Sydney.
      </h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Asteris Commerce builds Asteris for WooCommerce (a 20-module suite for WC stores), Asteris for WordPress (an 11-module suite for any WP site), and Asteris Cart (a 21-module checkout suite for WooCommerce). All four plugins replace stacks of separately-purchased competitors. All three are built by a small team, in active development, with launch-locked Founder pricing.
      </p>
      <p class="no-vc">
        No VC. No marketing team. No growth hacker, by design. A small team owning every line of code, every support reply, every roadmap call.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="products">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="prod-grid">
        <a href="https://asterisforwoocommerce.com" class="prod-card prod-card--wc" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          <div class="prod-meta">
            <div class="prod-eyebrow"><span class="prod-star">★</span> Asteris for WooCommerce</div>
            <span class="prod-status prod-status--live">Live · v1.0</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="prod-h">20 modules. One plugin. For every WooCommerce store.</h2>
          <p class="prod-desc">
            AI Suite, SEO, PDF Invoices, Variation Swatches, Wishlist, Quote/Enquiry, Back in Stock, Side Cart, Sequential Order Numbers, Product Filtering, Min/Max Quantity, Asteris Links, Trust Badges, Free Shipping Bar, Stock Urgency, Delivery Timeline, Feature Labels, Product Badges, Analytics (GA4 + GTM), and Asteris Coupons. All in one plugin. Replaces ~$1,650/yr of separate plugin licences (Yoast, YITH, WP Overnight, Skyverge, Iconic, Pretty Links and more). Built by a small team in Sydney against a documented Module Quality Protocol.
          </p>
          <ul class="prod-bullets">
            <li>All 20 modules at v1.0 (one plugin, one update cycle, one inbox)</li>
            <li>Free tier (6 modules) live on WordPress.org. SEO Lite, PDF Invoices Lite, Variation Swatches Lite, Product Filtering Lite, Sequential Order Numbers, Trust Badges</li>
            <li>Launch pricing locked for life of subscription. $149 / $349 / $549</li>
            <li>HPOS-verified, Block Cart compatible, tested on 6 themes (Storefront, Astra, GeneratePress, Elementor Hello, Divi, Bricks)</li>
            <li>One-click migration adapters from Yoast, YITH, WP Overnight, plus 3 others</li>
          </ul>
          <span class="prod-cta">Visit asterisforwoocommerce.com →</span>
        </a>

        <a href="https://asterisforwordpress.com" class="prod-card prod-card--wp" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          <div class="prod-meta">
            <div class="prod-eyebrow"><span class="prod-star">★</span> Asteris for WordPress</div>
            <span class="prod-status prod-status--dev">v1.0 · in active development</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="prod-h">11 modules. One plugin. For any WordPress site.</h2>
          <p class="prod-desc">
            Security + 2FA, SEO + AI, Performance, Forms, SMTP, Activity Log, Analytics + Pixels, Image Optimization, Backups + Migration, Code Snippets, and a WCAG accessibility scanner. All in one plugin. Replaces ~$1,100/yr of separate plugin licences. Built by a small team in Sydney against a documented Module Quality Protocol.
          </p>
          <ul class="prod-bullets">
            <li>All 11 modules at v1.0 (one plugin, one update cycle, one inbox)</li>
            <li>Free tier (6 modules) launching on WordPress.org</li>
            <li>Launch pricing locked for life of subscription. Founder 100 cohort plus 20 competition</li>
            <li>First-class integration with Gutenberg, Classic, Elementor, Bricks, Beaver Builder, Divi</li>
            <li>AI layer: llms.txt generator, IndexNow, AI bot management</li>
          </ul>
          <span class="prod-cta">Visit asterisforwordpress.com →</span>
        </a>

        <a href="https://asteriscart.com" class="prod-card prod-card--cart" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          <div class="prod-meta">
            <div class="prod-eyebrow"><span class="prod-star">★</span> Asteris Cart</div>
            <span class="prod-status prod-status--dev">In development · alpha</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="prod-h">21 modules. One plugin. For WooCommerce checkout.</h2>
          <p class="prod-desc">
            Side cart, free shipping bar, multi-step checkout, urgency timer, trust badges, GDPR consent, express checkout, quote mode, order bumps. All in one plugin. The honest alternative to CartFlows and FunnelKit. Built classic-hooks-first, HPOS-native from day one.
          </p>
          <ul class="prod-bullets">
            <li>21 modules at v1.0</li>
            <li>From $99/yr launch-locked (1 site)</li>
            <li>HPOS-native, Block Cart compatible</li>
            <li>Replaces ~$540/yr of CartFlows + FunnelKit + CheckoutWC</li>
          </ul>
          <span class="prod-cta">Visit asteriscart.com →</span>
        </a>

        <div class="prod-card prod-card--future prod-card--aff">
          <div class="prod-meta">
            <div class="prod-eyebrow"><span class="prod-star" style="color:#06D6A0;">★</span> Asteris Affiliates</div>
            <span class="prod-status prod-status--planned">v1.0 beta · open soon</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="prod-h">A full affiliate program for your store. No SaaS bill.</h2>
          <p class="prod-desc">
            AffiliateWP-grade features at SliceWP pricing. Multi-tier commissions, recurring renewals (WC Subscriptions), three payout methods (Stripe Connect, PayPal, encrypted bank transfer), 15 customisable email templates, refund-rate auto-suspend, magic-link affiliate portal. WP + WC. Replaces $300–$2,400/yr of AffiliateWP, Tapfiliate, Refersion.
          </p>
          <ul class="prod-bullets">
            <li>v1.1 ships MLM/two-tier, AI swipe-copy, A/B email tests, vanity landing pages</li>
            <li>Self-hosted — no per-affiliate SaaS fees, no transaction cuts</li>
            <li>EDD + Surecart adapters in addition to WC (any e-commerce platform)</li>
            <li>$149 / $299 / $549 — 1, 3, 10 sites · locked for life of subscription</li>
            <li>Free tier (planned): 1 site, up to 10 affiliates, manual payouts only</li>
          </ul>
          <span class="prod-cta">Visit asterisaffiliates.com →</span>
        </div>

        <div class="prod-card prod-card--blocks">
          <div class="prod-meta">
            <div class="prod-eyebrow"><span class="prod-star" style="color:#FFC107;">★</span> Asteris Blocks</div>
            <span class="prod-status prod-status--free">Free · WordPress.org</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="prod-h">50 free Gutenberg blocks. No upsells.</h2>
          <p class="prod-desc">
            The only fully-free Gutenberg block plugin from a real company. Hero, Pricing Table, FAQ with schema, Recipe Card with Recipe schema, Countdown, Cookie Notice, Code Block with syntax highlighting, Image Hotspots, Map, QR Code, Before/After Slider, Table of Contents — 50 blocks total, alphabetised, free forever. Replaces ~$400/yr of niche block plugins.
          </p>
          <ul class="prod-bullets">
            <li>50 blocks at v0.1 — no Pro tier, no nag, no lock</li>
            <li>Replaces MC4WP, FooGallery, HurryTimer, WP Recipe Maker, Cookie Notice, Author Box, Syntax Highlighter, Table of Contents, Social Share…</li>
            <li>Native typography + colour controls + HTML anchor IDs on every block</li>
            <li>Built-in cross-promo sidebar — funnels to the 4 paid Asteris plugins</li>
            <li>Free forever — locked decision, no future paywall</li>
          </ul>
          <span class="prod-cta">Visit asterisblocks.com →</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Mission strip · "Less cost, more inclusions" ────────────────────── -->
  <section class="mission-strip">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="mission-grid">
        <div class="mission-headline">
          <div class="mission-eyebrow">Our mission</div>
          <h2 class="mission-h">More inclusions. Less cost. Australian-built.</h2>
          <p class="mission-lead">
            One vendor relationship replaces stacks of paid plugins. Across the four products, we replace
            <strong>~$5,500/yr</strong> of competing tools for <strong>~$600–$2,000/yr</strong>.
            We're honest about what's in each plugin and what's not — no "Pro tier" surprises mid-trial.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="mission-table">
          <div class="mission-row mission-row--head"><span>Plugin</span><span>Replaces</span><span>Asteris price</span></div>
          <div class="mission-row"><span><strong>Asteris for WC</strong></span><span>~$1,500/yr</span><span>$149–$549/yr</span></div>
          <div class="mission-row"><span><strong>Asteris for WP</strong></span><span>~$1,100/yr</span><span>$149–$549/yr</span></div>
          <div class="mission-row"><span><strong>Asteris Cart</strong></span><span>~$540/yr</span><span>$99–$399/yr</span></div>
          <div class="mission-row"><span><strong>Asteris Affiliates</strong></span><span>$300–$2,400/yr</span><span>$149–$549/yr</span></div>
          <div class="mission-row"><span><strong>Asteris Blocks</strong></span><span>~$400/yr</span><span><strong>Free forever</strong></span></div>
          <div class="mission-row mission-row--total"><span><strong>Full stack</strong></span><span><strong>~$5,900/yr</strong></span><span><strong>~$600–$2,000/yr</strong></span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="why">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="why-inner">
        <h2>Why four plugins, one company</h2>
        <p>
          Most WordPress sites don't run WooCommerce. Most WooCommerce stores have plugin needs that go beyond what a generic WP plugin covers. And the WooCommerce checkout has its own deep stack of category-specific plugins (cart drawer, urgency, multi-step, express checkout, GDPR) that don't belong inside a general-purpose WC suite.
        </p>
        <p>
          All four products are built to the same standards but with sharply different scope. <strong>Asteris for WordPress</strong> covers what any WP site needs — security, SEO, backups, email. <strong>Asteris for WooCommerce</strong> covers what a WC store specifically needs — product page, conversion, fulfilment. <strong>Asteris Cart</strong> covers the checkout funnel itself — side cart, multi-step, urgency, express, GDPR, Quote Mode.
        </p>
        <p>
          Some modules genuinely overlap — SEO + AI, Analytics, Links, AI library, Activity Log. Those are built once and vendored across all four plugins, so the same code ships everywhere. Most modules don't overlap, which is why they're separate plugins instead of one mega-plugin nobody asked for.
        </p>
        <p>
          One company means one vendor relationship, one support inbox, one philosophy. Four plugins means each one stays focused on its actual buyer.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="about-strip">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="about-inner">
        <div class="about-text">
          <h3>About the company</h3>
          <p>
            Asteris Commerce is the plugin-products division of My Cosmic Message Pty Ltd, an Australian proprietary limited company (ACN 652 358 159, ABN 30 652 358 159) incorporated in 2021. Sole director Nick Lord, based in Sydney. The same Pty Ltd has been operating Orion Web Service (full-stack WP and WC development and hosting) since 2021. Asteris was built from five years of patterns observed running real client stores. No VC. No outside funding. No growth hacker. Funded by Orion Web Service revenue, plus Founder-tier subscriptions during launch, plus standing subscriptions thereafter.
          </p>
          <a href="/about" class="btn btn-large">Read more →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding: 80px 0 60px;
  }
  .eyebrow {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--c-yellow);
    padding: 4px 12px;
    border-radius: var(--r-sm);
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    color: var(--c-black);
  }
  h1 {
    font-size: 80px;
    line-height: 0.98;
    letter-spacing: -3px;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }
  .lead {
    font-size: 22px;
    color: #333;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }
  .lead strong { color: var(--c-black); }
  .no-vc {
    font-size: 17px;
    color: var(--c-muted);
    font-style: italic;
  }
  @media (max-width: 700px) { h1 { font-size: 48px; letter-spacing: -1.5px; } .lead { font-size: 17px; } }

  .products {
    padding: 40px 0 80px;
  }
  .prod-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 28px;
  }
  .prod-card {
    position: relative;
    background: var(--c-white);
    border: 2px solid var(--c-black);
    border-radius: var(--r-lg);
    padding: 32px;
    color: var(--c-text);
    transition: transform 0.1s ease, box-shadow 0.1s ease;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    border-top: 6px solid var(--tile-accent, var(--c-orange));
    --tile-accent: var(--c-orange);
  }
  .prod-card--wc { --tile-accent: #FF5B3F; }
  .prod-card--wp { --tile-accent: #3D5AFE; }
  .prod-card--cart { --tile-accent: #00C853; }
  .prod-card--future {
    --tile-accent: #AA00FF;
    opacity: 0.55;
    background: #fafafa;
    cursor: default;
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  /* Asteris Affiliates — teal accent, still greyed via opacity from --future */
  .prod-card--aff {
    --tile-accent: #06D6A0;
    border-color: #06D6A0;
  }
  /* Asteris Blocks — amber accent, FREE (not greyed) */
  .prod-card--blocks {
    --tile-accent: #FFC107;
    border-color: #FFC107;
  }
  .prod-status--free {
    background: #FFC107;
    color: #0a0a0a;
    font-weight: 700;
    border-color: #FFC107;
  }

  /* ── Mission strip ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .mission-strip {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0a0a0a 0%, #1a1a1a 100%);
    color: #fff;
    padding: 70px 0;
    border-top: 6px solid #AA00FF;
  }
  .mission-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 50px;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .mission-eyebrow {
    display: inline-block;
    background: #AA00FF;
    color: #fff;
    padding: 4px 12px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }
  .mission-h {
    font-size: 42px;
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -1.5px;
    margin: 0 0 18px;
    color: #fff;
  }
  .mission-lead {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: #d4d4d4;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .mission-lead strong { color: #06D6A0; }
  .mission-table {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 6px 0;
  }
  .mission-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.5fr 1fr 1.2fr;
    gap: 12px;
    padding: 12px 20px;
    font-size: 14px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
  }
  .mission-row:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
  .mission-row--head {
    color: #888;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .mission-row--total {
    background: rgba(6,214,160,0.08);
    border-top: 2px solid #06D6A0;
    border-bottom: 0;
    color: #06D6A0;
    font-size: 15px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .mission-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 30px; }
    .mission-h { font-size: 32px; letter-spacing: -1px; }
    .mission-row { grid-template-columns: 1.4fr 1fr 1fr; padding: 10px 14px; font-size: 13px; }
  }
  .prod-card:hover {
    transform: translate(-4px, -4px);
    box-shadow: 8px 8px 0 var(--tile-accent);
  }
  .prod-eyebrow {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--tile-accent);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
  }
  .prod-star {
    font-size: 22px;
    line-height: 1;
  }
  .prod-meta {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .prod-meta .prod-eyebrow { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .prod-status {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.6px;
    padding: 4px 10px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    border: 1.5px solid currentColor;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
    white-space: nowrap;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .prod-status--live { color: #2e7d32; }
  .prod-status--dev { color: #c0392b; }
  .prod-status--planned { color: #888888; }
  .prod-h {
    font-size: 30px;
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -1px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .prod-desc {
    font-size: 17px;
    color: #444;
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }
  .prod-bullets {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0 0 24px;
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--c-muted);
  }
  .prod-bullets li {
    padding: 4px 0;
    padding-left: 18px;
    position: relative;
  }
  .prod-bullets li::before {
    content: '✓';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--tile-accent);
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .prod-cta {
    margin-top: auto;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--tile-accent);
    font-size: 17px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 800px) {
    .prod-h { font-size: 26px; }
  }

  .why {
    background: var(--c-black);
    color: #cccccc;
    padding: 72px 0;
  }
  .why-inner h2 {
    color: var(--c-white);
    font-size: 36px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }
  .why-inner p {
    font-size: 22px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    color: #cccccc;
  }
  .why-inner p strong { color: var(--c-white); }

  .about-strip {
    padding: 80px 0;
  }
  .about-inner {
    /* full container width — matches the Why section above + product cards above that */
  }
  .about-inner h3 {
    font-size: 32px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .about-inner p {
    font-size: 22px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: #333;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }
  .about-inner p strong { color: var(--c-black); }
</style>
